$ /usr/local

According to the → Linux/fhs, `/usr/local` is for «for use by the system administrator when installing software locally».
Compare with `→ Linux/fhs/opt` and `→ Linux/fhs/usr`.

`→ development/GNU-Build-System/configure` chooses this directory as default for *architecture independent* 
(overwritable with `→ development/GNU-Build-System/configure#opt-prefix`) and *architecture dependent* files
(overwritable with `→ development/GNU-Build-System/configure#opt-exec-prefix`).
